StringBuffer        ==> its another class in Java which is used to create new strings

for eg,

    StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer("hii");

    sb.append(" noo");          sb ==> hii noo

StringBuffer , they are mutable

we can also do,

    sb.setCharAt(1,'I');
        sb==> hIi noo

        
        STRINGBUIDER ==> GOT NO CLUE DAHEC THAT iS